    <div id="sizes-options" class="dp-section">
      <h2>Luxury Swing Sizes, Hanging Options, and Upgrade Possibilities</h2>
      <p>
        Choosing the right swing for a Highland Park home is not only about appearance. It is also about scale, comfort, and how the swing will
        actually be used. Some spaces call for a compact custom porch swing. Others can support a large <strong>twin</strong> or
        <strong>full-size swing bed</strong> that feels more like a major outdoor furniture piece. Hanging style matters too. Rope tends to feel
        softer and more upscale. Chain can feel classic, timeless, and clean.
      </p>

      <ul class="dp-bullet-list">
        <li>
<strong>Crib size swings:</strong> ideal for tighter porches and smaller seating areas</li>
        <li>
<strong>Twin size swings:</strong> one of the most versatile sizes for comfort and proportion</li>
        <li>
<strong>Full size swings:</strong> best for homeowners wanting more presence and lounging space</li>
        <li>
<strong>Rope hanging:</strong> excellent for luxury, farmhouse, and pergola-style setups</li>
        <li>
<strong>Chain hanging:</strong> strong choice for classic front porch and timeless patio designs</li>
        <li>
<strong>Cushion-ready layouts:</strong> perfect for more comfort-focused outdoor living spaces</li>
      </ul>

